2019.04.15: Marius (GIVTK): I suggest to revise the definition of this concept. As of 2019-04-15, the definition is also applicable for formal languages, e.g. if one considers computers "participants" exchanging information using a language. My proposal: "System of human communication by speaking, writing, or making signs in a way that can be understood.". It is a slightly adapted version of the definitions given in the Cambridge Dictionary (https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english/language).
2019.04.15: Gökhan (GGVCM): Both proposals have been accepted. The changes have been done.
